Persian Gulf Stocks: Global Investment House and Saudi Telecom

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-09-05T13:14:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/persian-gulf-stocks-global-investment-house-and-saudi-telecom.html
Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  fell
0.4 percent at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate. Dubai’s  DFM
General Index (DFMGI)  decreased 0.3 percent, while Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  slid
1.6 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Global Investment House KSCC (GLOBAL)   rallied to the
highest in more than a month, surging 8.2 percent to 33 fils.
The Kuwait-based investment bank, which restructured $1.73
billion of debt in 2009, started initial talks with creditors on
the possibility of extending debt repayments, Al-Qabas reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Saudi Telecom Co. (STC)   dropped the most since Aug. 20,
losing 0.6 percent to 34 riyals. Saudi Arabia’s largest
telephone company by market value had its price estimate reduced
to 45.10 riyals from 50.90 riyals at Nomura Holdings Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
